bridge.n.01.defn: a structure that allows people or vehicles to cross an obstacle such as a river or canal or railway etc.

bridge.n.02.defn: a circuit consisting of two branches (4 arms arranged in a diamond configuration) across which a meter is connected

expl: his letters provided a bridge across the centuries
bridge.n.03.defn: something resembling a bridge in form or function

expl: her glasses left marks on the bridge of her nose
bridge.n.04.defn: the hard ridge that forms the upper part of the nose

bridge.n.05.defn: any of various card games based on whist for four players

bridge.n.06.defn: a wooden support that holds the strings up

bridge.n.07.defn: a denture anchored to teeth on either side of missing teeth

bridge.n.08.defn: the link between two lenses; rests on the nose

bridge.n.09.defn: an upper deck where a ship is steered and the captain stands

expl: they are having a special on pork chops
special.n.01.defn: a special offering (usually temporary and at a reduced price) that is featured in advertising

special.n.02.defn: a dish or meal given prominence in e.g. a restaurant

expl: the last of a series of BBC specials on Iran is being shown tonight
special.n.03.defn: a television production that features a particular person or work or topic

expl: the map showed roads and other features
generosity is one of his best characteristics
feature.n.01.defn: a prominent attribute or aspect of something

expl: an expression of pleasure crossed his features
feature.n.02.defn: the characteristic parts of a person's face: eyes and nose and mouth and chin

feature.n.03.defn: the principal (full-length) film in a program at a movie theater

expl: they ran a feature on retirement planning
feature.n.04.defn: a special or prominent article in a newspaper or magazine

feature_of_speech.n.01.defn: (linguistics) a distinctive characteristic of a linguistic unit that serves to distinguish it from other units of the same kind

feature.n.06.defn: an article of merchandise that is displayed or advertised more than other articles
